---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';

import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';
const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<BlogLayout title="Words Starting With QU- — Scrabble Prefix Scoring Guide" description="Master QU- prefix words in Scrabble. Find high-scoring quizzify, quixotic, and equalize plays with tips for deploying the Q tile effectively. Free tool." keywords="words starting with qu, scrabble qu words, qu prefix scrabble, high scoring qu words, quixotic scrabble, q tile strategy">

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">

    <!-- Article JSON-LD -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": "Words Starting With QU- — Scrabble Prefix Scoring Guide",
      "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/" }
    })} />

    <!-- FAQPage Schema -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring QU- words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QUIZZIFY scores 40 points, QUIXOTIC scores 26 points, and QUANTIZE scores 26 points. The QU- prefix alone gives you a base of 11 points (Q=10 + U=1)." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many valid QU- words exist in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 250 valid QU- words exist in the SOWPODS and TWL Scrabble dictionaries, ranging from 3 to 15 letters in length." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does Q always need U in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Q almost always needs U. Only a handful of Q-without-U words exist (like QI, QOPH, QADI, QANAT). QU- is the standard deployment pattern for the Q tile." } }
      ]
    })} />

    <!-- Hero -->
    <header class="text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">The Q tile is worth 10 points — the second highest in the game. Pair it with U and unlock over 250 powerful plays. Master QU- prefix words to turn Scrabble's trickiest tile into your biggest scoring weapon.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Stat Strip -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/30 rounded-xl p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300">11 pts</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">Base (Q10 + U1)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/30 rounded-xl p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300">250+</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">Valid Words</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/30 rounded-xl p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300">3–15</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">Letter Range</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- High-Scoring Table -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Top Scoring QU- Words</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Length</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Key Tiles</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUIZZIFY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">40</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+Z(10)+Z(10)+F(4)+Y(4)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUIZZING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">36</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+Z(10)+Z(10)+G(2)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">SQUEEZY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">28</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+Z(10)+Y(4)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUARTZITE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">27</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+Z(10) rock</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUIXOTIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">26</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+X(8)+C(3)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUANTIZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">26</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+Z(10) double</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUICKLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+K(5)+Y(4)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUALIFY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">22</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Q(10)+F(4)+Y(4)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Card Grid -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">QU- Word Categories</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 dark:text-green-300 mb-2">Common QU- Words</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">QUEEN, QUIET, QUICK, QUOTE, QUEST, QUITE</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 mb-2">Scientific / Technical</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400">QUANTUM, QUARTZ, QUARANTINE, QUADRANT, QUININE</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-800 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 mb-2">Rare High-Value</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QUIXOTIC, QUIZZIFY, QUANTIZE, QUINZHEE, QUILTZ</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 mb-2">Short QU- Forms</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">QUA, QUAD, QUAY, QUIZ, QUOD, QUIP</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pills -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Quick QU- Plays</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUA <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">12 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUAY <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">16 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUIZ <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">22 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUIP <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">15 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUOD <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-4 py-2 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40 text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 rounded-full font-semibold text-sm">QUAD <span class="text-purple-500 dark:text-purple-400 font-normal">14 pts</span></span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Strategy Tips -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Strategy Tips for QU- Words</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border-l-4 border-purple-500 rounded-r-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 mb-1">Deploy Q Early</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">Q is 10 points but devastating if stuck with at end-game (-10 penalty). Play QU- words in the first half of the game. Even a simple QUIZ (22 pts) gets Q off your rack safely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border-l-4 border-purple-500 rounded-r-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 mb-1">Premium Square Targeting</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">Q on a double letter = 20 pts from one tile. On triple letter = 30 pts. Always position QU- plays to land Q on premium squares — the difference is enormous.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border-l-4 border-purple-500 rounded-r-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-300 mb-1">Know Q-Without-U</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">QI (11), QOPH (18), QADI (14), QANAT (14) don't need U. But QU- is still your primary strategy since U is common (4 in bag) and opens 250+ words.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cross Links -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Related Prefix Guides</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-ex/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/30 text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 dark:hover:bg-indigo-900/50 transition-colors text-sm font-medium">Words Starting With EX- →</a>
        <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-un/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/30 text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 dark:hover:bg-indigo-900/50 transition-colors text-sm font-medium">Words Starting With UN- →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Articles -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">More Prefix Guides</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/blog/words-starting-with-re/" class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 hover:underline">Words Starting With RE- →</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/words-starting-with-super/" class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 hover:underline">Words Starting With SUPER- →</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/words-starting-with-anti/" class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 hover:underline">Words Starting With ANTI- →</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <BlogCrossLinks title="Words Starting With QU — Scrabble Guide" />

    <!-- Additional content for threshold -->
    <section class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Mastering the Q Tile</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">The Q tile is the most feared tile in Scrabble for a reason: 10 points if you play it, -10 points if you're stuck with it at game end. QU- is your primary exit strategy. By knowing 250+ QU- words, you transform Q from a liability into your biggest scoring weapon.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">Always play Q in the first half of the game when possible. Premium squares are more available early, and you avoid the end-game penalty risk. Even a simple QUIZ (22 points without premiums) is a strong play that clears Q off your rack.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">When Q lands on a double letter square, it's worth 20 points from that single tile. On a triple letter, 30 points. Position your QU- plays to maximize premium square hits — the difference between QUIZ on a normal square (22) versus Q on TLS (42) is enormous.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">If you draw Q without U, don't panic. QI (11 pts), QOPH (18 pts), QADI (14 pts), and QANAT (14 pts) are your lifelines. But prevention is better — when you see U on your rack, consider holding it in case Q arrives next draw.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500 to-orange-500 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Find Every QU- Word From Your Tiles</h2>
        <p class="text-amber-100 mb-5">Enter your tiles and find every QU- word instantly</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-white text-amber-700 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    
<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Building Your Word Arsenal</h2>

<p>The difference between a 300-point game and a 400-point game often comes down to vocabulary depth. Players who invest time studying valid Scrabble words consistently outscore those who rely solely on common everyday vocabulary. The words on this page represent a focused subset of the Scrabble dictionary that you can realistically memorise and deploy in competitive play.</p>

<p>Start by identifying which words on this page you already know. Then focus your study time on the unfamiliar ones — particularly those with high point values or unusual letter combinations. The goal is not to memorise the entire dictionary but to build a working vocabulary of 5,000-10,000 words that covers the most common game situations.</p>

<p>Consider keeping a word journal where you record new discoveries from each study session. Writing words down activates different memory pathways than simply reading them. Many tournament players carry small notebooks and review their most recent additions during breaks between rounds.</p>


<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Applying These Words in Real Games</h2>

<p>Knowing a word exists and successfully playing it in a game are two different skills. The bridge between them is pattern recognition — training your brain to spot opportunities for specific words when you see certain tile combinations on your rack. This comes through deliberate practice rather than passive memorisation.</p>

<p>When you study the words on this page, visualise how they would fit on a Scrabble board. Which premium squares could they reach? What letters would they need to hook onto? How many tiles from a typical rack would they consume? This kind of active visualisation builds the neural pathways that fire automatically during timed games.</p>

<p>One effective technique is to take each word and mentally construct the rack you would need to play it. Then ask yourself: if I drew those tiles, would I recognise the word opportunity immediately? If the answer is no, that word needs more study time. If yes, move on to the next unfamiliar word in your list.</p>

<p>Tournament players often practice with a specific study goal — for example, spending one week focused exclusively on 5-letter words containing a particular letter pattern, then the following week on 6-letter words. This structured approach prevents the overwhelm of trying to learn everything simultaneously.</p>

<div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
      <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
    </div>

  </article>
</BlogLayout>
